               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">EDWARD</hi> Fox. On Friday evening, the 29th of May, I was walking in St. Paul's Church-yard—I felt something at my pocket—I turned, and saw the prisoner walking very deliberately—I could not think it was him—some labouring man told me that he had taken my handkerchief—I took him—he at first denied it; he then gave it up to me, and begged I would let him go—this is my handkerchief.</p>
